metadata.name: Tao
metadata.description:
Tao is the eternal action or principle of creation, which is responsible for exclusiveness and duality, and at the same time for the beginning of the world and creation.

This piece is the first piece  of the series of four works dedicated to Ouroboros - an ancient symbol depicting a snake eating its own tail.

It symbolize the eternal cyclic renewal or a cycle of life, death, and rebirth.

The collection is created in a mixed media technique that connects real life shootings and computer graphics. 
CG is created in collaboration with 3D Artist Petr Boroda
